<collectingRegion id="0650F81CFF666AD9FCEF95361D42B8BE" box="[787,834,879,908]" country="South Sudan" name="Lakes" pageId="157" pageNumber="918">See</collectingRegion>
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF666AD9FCAE95361DD1B8BE" box="[850,977,879,908]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Murina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="157" pageNumber="917" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="fionae">M. fionae</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF666AD9FC1A95361AF5B8BE" authorityName="Hill" authorityYear="1964" box="[998,1269,879,908]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Murina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="157" pageNumber="918" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="peninsularis">Murina peninsularis</taxonomicName>
was recently elevated to a distinct species based on genetic and morphological data. It might represent multiple species, with a second species in Borneo that is highly divergent from other populations of 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF666AD9FAFD926D1D86BF4B" authorityName="Hill" authorityYear="1964" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Murina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="157" pageNumber="918" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="peninsularis">M. peninsularis</taxonomicName>
. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
